author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: AREA ROUNDUP: Wayne girls soccer eliminates Canandaigua
text: Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 10:33 PM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 10:33 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. WAYNE — The Canandaigua girls soccer team fell to Wayne in the second round of the Class A sectional playoffs on Wednesday. The Eagles’ Hannah Mitchell scored two first half goals to give Wayne all it needed. Adrianna VanCuyck finished the game with two goals and two assists and Taylor Gabriel added a goal for Wayne. The No. 2 Eagles were led in goal by Bailey Jenkins, who made four saves and recorded the shutout. No. 15 Canandaigua finishes the season with a 3-14 record. Wayne will play the winner of No. 10 Brockport and No. 7 Aquinas on Saturday. In other high school girls soccer action on Wednesday: CLASS D1 No. 7 Mount Morris 2, No. 10 Honeoye 1 Sara Jane Stevens scored the lone goal of the game for the Bulldogs. Mount Morris’ Lauren Ferraro scored both goals for the Blue Devils. BOYS SOCCER CLASS B1 No. 9 Waterloo 4, No. 8 Midlakes 0 Payton Rodgers scored two goals to lead the Indians over the Screaming Eagles. Brady Adair added two assists for Waterloo. TUESDAY’S LATE RESULTS GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Canandaigua 3, Pittsford Mendon 0 The Braves (6-8) defeated Mendon 26-24, 25-16 and 25-13. Rachel Simmons had eight kills and three aces and Carli Lenz added five kills and six blocks for Canandaigua. Cami Smeatin added five kills and three blocks for the Braves and Nicole Mendick led Mendon with 18 assists and five digs. By Messenger Post
